question = Question.create(catagory_id: catagory.id, topic_id: topic.id, question_num: "3", question_content: "What kind of bridges are these?", question_image: "section_images/different_types_of_bridges_subset_small.png",explanation: "A beam is a horizontal structural element supported on both ends. With bridges, this beam is called a span. A beam bridge can have a single span or it can be continuous and have many spans and therefore many supports. A suspension bridge supports its deck with a pair of cables. These two cables run along the top of two towers and are then anchored to the earth at each end. Suspender cables attach the deck to these top two cables. An arch bridge works by diverting the force of its load to abutments on either side of the arch. An arch bridge can be designed as a single arch with a deck on top, or as a series of arches that are connected with a deck on top. Arch bridges can also be built with the span of the deck passing through the arch, called a through arch bridge. ")
